notes: The crown worn on the helmet indicates a king (cp. l. 1123: “ein kunec, geriten in sin lant”)
All helmets depicted in the illustrations are of the type called
(en. ‘pot helm’ or ‘great helm’), which was used between 1200 and 1250 (Gichtel, pp. 80-81)
The knight lances are represented with a simple pen stroke
Cp. l. 1280: “ein sloz si vür die tür do stiez”
Blanscheflur wears a brown garb used by beggars (cp. l. 1267: “eines armen betewibes cleit”)
